# Marketing and UI copy

Write like a **finished product**, not a build log or internal doc.

## Do

- Short, clear sentences. State what the user **gets** or **does**.
- Professional SaaS tone (Stripe, FreshBooks style).
- Nepal wholesaler context where relevant (godown, VAT, accountant export).

## Do not (in user-visible text)

- Phase 0 / P1 / first launch / second launch / deferred / roadmap
- “Partial”, “optional feature”, “if enabled”, “per tenant”, “shipped today”
- “Not part of launch”, “coming soon”, migration numbers, schema cache, RPC names
- “We built…”, “Modules shipped…”, “Replace placeholder…”, file paths
- Long negatives listing what the product is **not** (retail POS, pharma, etc.)

## FAQ / pricing

- Say what **is included** or **how it works**.
- For gaps (e.g. IRD e-filing): one calm line — e.g. “not included in the app today” — not “not part of first launch”.

## Errors

- User message: plain English + phone/WhatsApp if needed. No README or migration IDs.
